headline: Jabil (JBL): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Jabil currently trades at $220.68 and has been a dream stock for shareholders. It’s returned 529% since August 2020, blowing past the S&P 500’s 89.1% gain. The company has also beaten the index over the past six months as its stock price is up 33.4% thanks to its solid quarterly results.
